    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"609515\">@Kevin Carlson</span>  and I just posted our paper on characterizations of exponentiable virtual double categories last week: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20586\">https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.20586</a></p>\n<p>This work arose late last summer out of a desire to understand higher morphisms and enrichments for virtual double categories (VDCs). We initially discovered a characterization of exponentiable VDCs, and morphisms of such more generally, in terms of a Conduche-like condition for decompositions of multicells, as described back <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CLwKSyVtjLc\">in this talk in the Topos Institute Berkeley Seminar</a>. This characterization led to simple constructions of a number of families of exponentiable VDCs, including those representable by pseudo-double categories and those arising as cospans in arbitrary categories.</p>\n<div class=\"youtube-video message_inline_image\"><a data-id=\"CLwKSyVtjLc\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CLwKSyVtjLc\"><img src=\"https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/b2f912fd2e063941bec2cba6c46aa20a72ac9fb4/68747470733a2f2f692e7974696d672e636f6d2f76692f434c774b537956746a4c632f6d7164656661756c742e6a7067\"></a></div><p>Since this initial characterization we've expanded our classification to address a conjecture in a recent paper of Arkor's (<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.11611v2\">https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.11611v2</a>), while also providing a characterization in terms of decompositions involving only binary, unary, and nullary multicells. This most recent characterization provides an effective framework for testing and constructing exponentiable VDCs.</p>\n<p>At the end of the paper we dig deeper into this theory of exponentiable VDCs to begin understanding when the resulting exponentials are representable by pseudo-double categories, or more generally when they have weak composites, using a similar treatment to that of Paré in the case of pseudo-double categories. </p>\n<p>As an example, these characterizations allowed us to show that for any VDC <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span></span></span></span>, we have a yoneda type embedding <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo>↪</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">S</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>o</mi><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow></msup></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}\\hookrightarrow \\mathbb{S}\\mathsf{pan}^{\\mathsf{fc}(\\mathbb{D})^{op_t}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6999em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0824em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">S</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">pan</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.888em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathsf mtight\">fc</span></span><span class=\"mopen mtight\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb mtight\">D</span><span class=\"mclose mtight\"><span class=\"mclose mtight\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.7385em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3448em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.3448em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.1em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.6151em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2703em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> into a locally cocomplete VDC with non-nullary composites, where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathsf{fc}(\\mathbb{D})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">fc</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> is the free strict double category on the VDC <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span></span></span></span>. Additionally, if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span></span></span></span> has loose units, then a choice of such provides an embedding into a locally cocomplete pseudo-double category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo>↪</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">V</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>o</mi><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">S</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">n</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}\\hookrightarrow \\mathbb{V}\\mathsf{df}(\\mathsf{fc}(\\mathbb{D})^{op_t},\\mathbb{S}\\mathsf{pan})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6999em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">V</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0694em;\">df</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">fc</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2963em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.357em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.143em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">S</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">pan</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. In particular, we can freely add loose units to an arbitrary VDC <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6889em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span></span></span></span>, giving us the ability to embed arbitrary VDCs into locally cocomplete pseudo-double categories <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo>↪</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">F</mi><mi>u</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>↪</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">V</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">d</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">f</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">c</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">F</mi><mi>u</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">D</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>o</mi><msub><mi>p</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow></msup><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">S</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"sans-serif\">n</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{D}\\hookrightarrow\\mathbb{F}_u(\\mathbb{D})\\hookrightarrow \\mathbb{V}\\mathsf{df}(\\mathsf{fc}(\\mathbb{F}_u(\\mathbb{D}))^{op_t},\\mathbb{S}\\mathsf{pan})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6999em;vertical-align:-0.011em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">F</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">u</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">↪</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">V</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\" style=\"margin-right:0.0694em;\">df</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">fc</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">F</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">u</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">D</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2963em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.357em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.0714em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.5em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.143em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">S</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathsf\">pan</span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>. We're hoping to investigate the universal property of such embeddings in future work.</p>",
        "id": 597419800,
        "sender_full_name": "Ea E T (they/she)",
        "timestamp": 1779647056
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Found a few typos:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Corollary 3.5: wrong parentheses and arrow in the introduction of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>λ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span></span></span></span>.</li>\n<li>Definition 3.6: \"first for\" -&gt; \"first four\".</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 597716869,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1779760796
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It seems like the techniques can be extended to algebras of other accessible monads on presheaf categories, as they are based on limit sketches.  I'm not sure how much the nice theorem on limit sketches would be mangled by pulling it back across the interpretation of accessible monads on presheaf categories as limit sketches though.</p>",
        "id": 597717982,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1779761172
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(In particular, it seems like Burroni/Leinster-style $T$-categories on p.r.a. monads $T$ probably <em>could</em> be treated pretty uniformly, though, as the Leinster \"plus\" construction heavily constrains its resulting monad.</p>",
        "id": 597718194,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1779761297
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"438995\">James Deikun</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/274877-community.3A-our-work/topic/Ea.20E.20Thompson/near/597718194\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>(In particular, it seems like Burroni/Leinster-style $T$-categories on p.r.a. monads $T$ probably <em>could</em> be treated pretty uniformly, though, as the Leinster \"plus\" construction heavily constrains its resulting monad.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes! The main challenging step in this process is understanding what the colimits in models look like. In the case of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-multicategories one can use that the theory category is fibered over the simplex category to perform a similar argument to that in our paper to construct an explicit pre-sheaf model for the colimit using left Kan extensions of pre-sheaves. We originally didn't pursue this since we were told that Lack and Fujii were currently working on the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-multicategory setting, and our applications of interest were primarily in the case of VDCs. </p>\n<p>However, this approach was used in the setting of quasi-categories to give precisely this kind of characterization in the recent pre-print <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.29815v2\">https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.29815v2</a> (although binary-nullary reductions aren't considered there). We are hoping to perform a similar characterization for certain special classes of limit sketches, such as those for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-algebras when <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span> is a p.r.a monad on a pre-sheaf category, since the natural embedding of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-algebras in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.1389em;\">T</span></span></span></span>-multicategories does not reflect exponentiable morphisms.</p>",
        "id": 598135691,
        "sender_full_name": "Ea E T (they/she)",
        "timestamp": 1779900443
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact it makes all the morphisms exponentiable!  Can't really complain about it, since it's nice having a small embedding that adds exponentials to all the existing morphisms!</p>",
        "id": 598171700,
        "sender_full_name": "James Deikun",
        "timestamp": 1779911890
    }
]